'''Eärendil''' ([[Quenya]]: "sea-friend", pron. {{IPA|[ˌe.aˈrendil]}}) can refer to the following:

* '''[[Eärendil]] (born {{FA|503}}), the great hero of the [[First Age]] who sailed to [[Valinor]] with a [[Silmaril]].'''
** [[Star of Eärendil]], the [[Silmaril]] that shines as a star in the night sky.
** ''[[Eärendillinwë]]'', a poem in ''[[The Fellowship of the Ring]]'' about [[Eärendil]] written by [[Bilbo Baggins]].
* [[Eärendil (King of Gondor)|Eärendil]] ({{TA|238}} - {{TA|324|n}}), the fifth [[Kings of Gondor|King]] of [[Gondor]].

* The [[Elessar of Eärendil]], a fabulous gem of the [[First Age|First]] and [[Third Age|Third]] Ages.
*''[[Aiya Eärendil elenion ancalima!]]'', a cry in [[Quenya]].
